         <abstract>
            <p>Robert Crouch has argued in this Journal for a model in which the flow of news to the market determines both stock prices and trading volume. Testing his model, the authors find evidence that macroeconomic news plays a special role in the determination of exchange volume.</p>
          </abstract>
